"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541255","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-05","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my predecessor (Philip Dunne) on 27 June 2016 to Question 40450 to the hon. Member for Glasgow South West (Chris Stephens).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-09-05T14:54:45.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541255/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541255/answer","20160627_40450_Type_26_Frigates[1].docx","40450 - QnA extract on Type 26 Frigates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541255/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-07-20","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the current budget is for the Type 26 Frigate programme.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","43689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541256","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-07","<p>We have begun the initial pre-concept work to take forward the new General Purpose Frigate (GPFF) programme outlined in the White Paper 'National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015'. The work is in the very early stages and it is too early to say what either the build strategy or the detailed supply chain arrangements may be.</p><p>In addition, as part of his work leading the National Shipbuilding Strategy, Sir John Parker will be considering how to balance the GPFF requirement against export opportunities and industrial capacity.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","43692","2016-09-07T14:27:45.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541256/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541256/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541256/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-07-20","Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps is he taking to ensure that the General Purpose Frigate programme leverages the wider supply chain built up for the Queen Elizabeth-class carrier programme and takes advantage of skills in design, engineering, manufacturing, integration, and assurance resident outside BAE Systems.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","43690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541257","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-07","<p>We have begun the initial pre-concept work to take forward the new General Purpose Frigate (GPFF) programme outlined in the White Paper 'National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015'. The work is in the very early stages and it is too early to say what either the build strategy or the detailed supply chain arrangements may be.</p><p>In addition, as part of his work leading the National Shipbuilding Strategy, Sir John Parker will be considering how to balance the GPFF requirement against export opportunities and industrial capacity.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","43690","2016-09-07T14:27:45.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541257/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541257/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541257/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-07-20","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he expects that the build facilities selected as the build location for both the Type 26 frigate programme and the General Purpose Frigate will be able to deliver both platforms concurrently.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","43692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541258","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-09-05","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my predecessor (Philip Dunne) on 27 June 2016 to Question 39922 to the hon. Member for Portsmouth South (Mrs Flick Drummond).</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-09-05T14:50:26.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541258/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541258/answer","Hansard_Extract_27_June_2016_HOC_39922.[1].docx","39922 - QnA extract on Type 23 Frigates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541258/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-07-20","Type 26 Frigates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he has had with the Royal Navy about further extending the out-of-service dates for the Type 23 frigate.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","43693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541259","Department for Education","false","2016-11-01","<p>The Education Funding Agency is due to publish a report about Bright Tribe Trust. This final report will include the Trust’s progress in implementing recommendations set out by the EFA in December 2015; and will incorporate how assurance is obtained that services are provided at cost. Once this report is published, a copy will be placed in the Library.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","43736 ; 43737","2016-11-01T13:36:43.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541259/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541259/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541259/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-20","Bright Tribe Multi-academy Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will place in the Library a copy of the report about Bright Tribe Multi-Academy Trust prepared by the Risk Analysis Division of the Education Funding Agency.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","43738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541260","Department for Education","false","2016-11-01","<p>The Education Funding Agency is due to publish a report about Bright Tribe Trust. This final report will include the Trust’s progress in implementing recommendations set out by the EFA in December 2015; and will incorporate how assurance is obtained that services are provided at cost. Once this report is published, a copy will be placed in the Library.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","43736 ; 43738","2016-11-01T13:36:43.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541260/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541260/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/541260/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-07-20","Adventure Learning Academy Trust and Bright Tribe Multi-academy Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will place in the Library copies of the action plans by Bright Tribe Multi-Academy Trust and Adventure Learning Academies Trust in response to the request made to them by the Education Funding Agency.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","43737"
